**JUST WANT TO GET IMPLEMENTATION JUMP TO CODE**

Basic property of bst is that it contains its left child as smaller or equal to node and its right child greater to it,(the equal child can be kept any of the side).


in the given diagram 
									10
									/   \\
								5          15
							   /  \\           \\
							 3       7           18
the node value(10) is in given range therefore the possibilty of having a in-range value on both subtrees  is possible,
therefore we take a extra memory(taking queue) and add both its child to it
Queue has 5,15 now .
picking 5(as of fifo).
now 5 is smaller than the lower value but its right child can have a value greater to it which might be in  given range,so we eliminate the left subtree and add the right child of it to the queue.

now,queue become 15,7.
as 15 is in range we"ll again add both of its child to queue.
and the process goes....
the moment we get a node in given range we take the sum of it and add it to a variable.


**CODE**
```
class Solution {
public:
    int rangeSumBST(TreeNode* root, int low, int high) {
          if(root==NULL)return 0;
        queue<TreeNode*>q;
        int res=0;
        q.push(root);
        while(!q.empty())
        {
            TreeNode*temp=q.front();
            q.pop();
            if(temp->val<low)
            {
                if(temp->right!=NULL)q.push(temp->right);
            }
            else if(temp->val>high)
            {
                if(temp->left!=NULL)q.push(temp->left);
            }

            else if(temp->val>=low&&temp->val<=high)
            {
                res+=temp->val;
                if(temp->left!=NULL)q.push(temp->left);
                if(temp->right!=NULL)q.push(temp->right);   
            }


        }
        return res;

    }
};
```

