solutions.content:
Design a stack with the following operations:

* `CustomStack(int maxSize)`: initialize the stack with `maxSize`
* `void push(int x)`: Adds `x` to the top of the stack if the size doesn't reach `maxSize`
* `int pop()`: return the top of the stack and pop it, or return -1 when it is empty
* `void inc(int k, int val)`: increase the bottom `min(k, size)` elements of the stack by `val`

# Explanation

Since the constraints are small (`1 <= maxSize <= 1000`, at most 1000 calls), just simulate the whole process.

# C++ Solution

```cpp
class CustomStack {
    int maxSize;
    vector<int> stk;
public:
    CustomStack(int maxSize) {
        this->maxSize = maxSize;
    }

    void push(int x) {
        if (stk.size() < maxSize)
            stk.push_back(x);
    }

    int pop() {
        if (stk.size() > 0) {
            int x = stk.back();
            stk.pop_back();
            return x;
        }
        return -1;
    }

    void increment(int k, int val) {
        for (int i = 0; i < min(k, (int) stk.size()); i++)
            stk[i] += val;
    }
};
```

