ok lets do this!!
we have to implement a stack where some operations are to be done-pop,push,increment etc!

note- i see many people using a stack to solve to solve this question!i am not going to do that because i feel that is absurd because you are already using predefined functions like push() and pop() ,which the question doesnt ask!
the question asks us to implement a stack!
i am going to show two data structures that you can do to simulate the stack operations!

APPROACH 1-
USING ARRAY!

1>we take an array which we initialise with size as maaxSize
2>we also take an pointer initialy set to -1;
3>so that whenever underflow condition occurs we print -1
