# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
 - Since, array provides the functionality of random access, which is performed in $$O(1)$$ time, we can easily implement the ```push()```, ```pop()``` functions in $$O(1)$$.
 - Though ```increment()``` will take $$O(k)$$ because we have to traverse first k elements *(if k < list.length)* in order to increment them.
 - Maintaining ```idx``` becomes important since indices from ```0``` to ```idx``` represent the actual **stack**.

