Here we have to keep track of no of elements in stack so i have used count variable which gives no of elements in stack at current time.

And size variable will be used to check the maximum size of stack.

```
class CustomStack {
    Stack<Integer> stack;
    int size;
    int count = 0;

    public CustomStack(int maxSize) {
        stack = new Stack<>();
        this.size = maxSize;
    }

    public void push(int x) {
        if(count < size) {
            stack.push(x);
            count++;
        }
    }

    public int pop() {
        if(stack.empty())
            return -1;
        else {
            count--;
            return stack.pop();
        }
    }

    public void increment(int k, int val) {

	// If total no of elements is less than k then we have to increment all elements of stack.
	// else we have to increment from i=0 to i=k which are last k bottom elements of stack.
        if(count < k) {
            for(int i=0; i<count; i++) {
                stack.set(i, stack.get(i)+val);
            }
        } else {
            for(int i=0; i<k; i++)
                stack.set(i, stack.get(i)+val);
        }
    }
}
```

