***1.) Bit Manipulation :
Explanation :*** 📊
**In the ASCII TABLE :**
***Range of Capital letters |₁₀ : A to Z***  ( from **65**(***A***) to **90**(***Z***) )
***Range of Cursive/ Small letters |₁₀ : a to z*** (from **97**(***a***) to **122**(***z***));

Using Double for loop for iterating over every substring : 
***Condition :  if (s[j]>='a')***  means s[j] is ***lowercase***.
***else*** it is ***uppercase***

***(1<<(s[j]-'a'))***  : convert to integer .
Eg : ***string s= abcABC*** 
***a***-> 0 , ***b***-> 1, ***c***->2 (in integer)
***A***-> 0 , ***B***-> 1, ***C***->2 (in integer)
***exor :*** 1^2^3^1^2^3 =0  , Therefore , it is a ***valid*** string .

**UPVOTE IF YOU LIKE** 😇✅
```

class Solution {
public:
    string longestNiceSubstring(string s) {
        int maxLength=0,idx=0;  // idx stores the starting index of the substring
        int lowerCase,upperCase;
        for (int i=0;i<s.length();i++)
        {
            lowerCase=0;
            upperCase=0;
            for (int j=i;j<s.length();j++)
            {
                if (s[j]>='a')
                    lowerCase|=(1<<(s[j]-'a'));
                else 
                    upperCase|=(1<<(s[j]-'A'));
                if ((lowerCase^upperCase)==0)
                {
                    if (maxLength<j-i+1)
                    {
                        idx=i;
                        maxLength=j-i+1;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        if (maxLength==0)
            return "";
        return s.substr(idx,maxLength);
    }
};
```
***2.) Divide and Conquer  Approach :
Explanation :*** 🔑
Firstly  ,we store all characters in the set (no duplicates ) for O(1) access.
If for a char in lower case , the corresponding uppercase is not present , and vis a vis , 
we cannot include it in answer, 
->We divide string int substring . ***(Standard Divide and Conquer Structure )*** ✌️
->Select the string with larger length . 
->Combine and return  the resultant string.
```
class Solution {
public:
    string longestNiceSubstring(string s) {
        if(s.length()<2)return "";

        unordered_set<char>set(s.begin(), s.end()); // store all the characters of string s

        for(int i=0; i<s.length(); ++i){
            // if corresponding upper or lower character not present we know it will
            // never be present in our answer substring
            if(set.find(toupper(s[i]))==set.end() || set.find(tolower(s[i]))==set.end()){
			   //Divide and Conquer step :
                string s1 = longestNiceSubstring(s.substr(0, i));
                string s2 = longestNiceSubstring(s.substr(i+1));
                return s1.size() >= s2.size() ? s1 : s2;
            }
        }

        return s; // whole string is the answer
    }
};
```

