Use two for-loops to check every possible substring.
For each substring, keep tracking which lowercase and uppercase characters are seen.

```
class Solution {
    public String longestNiceSubstring(String s) {
        int start = 0, end = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            boolean[] upper = new boolean[26];
            boolean[] lower = new boolean[26];
            for(int j = i; j < s.length(); j++) {
                char c = s.charAt(j);
                if('a' <= c && c <= 'z') lower[c - 'a'] = true;
                if('A' <= c && c <= 'Z') upper[c - 'A'] = true;
                if(Arrays.equals(lower, upper) && end-start < j-i+1) {
                    start = i;
                    end = j+1;
                }
            }
        }
        return s.substring(start, end);
    }
}
```

Time: ```O(N^2)```
Space: ```O(1)```

